OL,3,C'It shouldn't happen': Disabled people
OL,4,Ccriticise poor access in town
OL,6,FPeople living with disabilities in
OL,7,FGuernsey have spoken out over 'near
OL,8,Fmisses' which they say are caused by
OL,9,Fnarrow pavements on the island.
OL,11,FThey want pedestrian routes to be made
OL,12,Fmore accessible as they face several
OL,13,Fsafety issues including cars on
OL,14,Fpavements, cobbles and high curbs
OL,15,Fwhich make it hard to get around
OL,16,Feasily.
OL,18,FSimon De La Mare is visually impaired
OL,19,Fand relies on his guide dog Cyril to
OL,20,Fnavigate the streets.
