OL,3,C'It shouldn't happen': Disabled people
OL,4,Ccriticise poor access in town
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Martine White uses a
OL,7,Fmobility scooter and explains: "If you
OL,8,Fcan still fit on the pavement, you are
OL,9,Falways over-hanging on the edge and if
OL,10,Fyou can't, you have to dismount.
OL,12,F"The problem is there is not a dropped
OL,13,Fpavement anywhere, it shouldn't
OL,14,Fhappen. People shouldn't be stranded
OL,15,Fbecause of issues like this.
OL,17,F"People shouldn't have to feel like
OL,18,Fthey are taking on a battle."
